edu.cornell.gdiac.starstruck

Class LevelSelectModel

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.cornell.gdiac.starstruck.LevelSelectModel

  • public class LevelSelectModel
extends java.lang.Object
    Represents a single level in our game Note that the constructor does very little. The true initialization happens by reading the JSON value. To reset a level, dispose it and reread the JSON. The level contains its own Box2d World, as the World settings are defined by the JSON file. However, there is absolutely no controller code in this class, as the majority of the methods are getters and setters. The getters allow the GameController class to modify the level elements.
